I think the treatment of the universal joint axes is not yet correct. From [UniversalJoint.hh](#!/osrf/gazebo/src/7298099ad5967af3b9207ae93ae309ee861fd31c/gazebo/physics/UniversalJoint.hh?at=default#cl-31):
~~~
    /// Axis1 and axis2 are body-fixed, with axis1 attached to parent
    /// body and axis2 attached to child body.
~~~
We need to attach Axis1 to the parent body. Currently both are attached to the child body. For an example model, see [cart_front_steer](#!/osrf/gazebo_models/src/a4175046689342c55dfc1128f3a318e1634adca1/cart_front_steer/), which has universal joints at the front wheels. The vertical steering axis shouldn't rotate with the wheels as it rolls forwards or backwards.
